\begin{align*} \cos^2 (x + y) &= (\cos x \cos y - \sin x \sin y)^2 \\ &= \cos^2 x \cos^2 y - 2 \cos x \cos y \cos (x + y) + \sin^2 x \sin^2 y. \end{align*} 
Substituting this into the original expression, we obtain 
\begin{align*} \cos^2 x + \cos^2 (x + y) - 2 \cos x \cos y \cos (x + y) &= \cos^2 x + \cos^2 x \cos^2 y - 2 \cos x \cos y \cos (x + y) \\ &\quad + \sin^2 x \sin^2 y - 2 \cos x \cos y \cos (x + y) \\ &= \cos^2 x (1 + \cos^2 y) + \sin^2 x (1 - \cos^2 y) - 4 \cos x \cos y \cos (x + y) \\ &= \cos^2 x + \sin^2 x - 4 \cos^2 y \cos^2 x \cos^2 (x + y) \\ &= 1 - 4 \cos^2 y \cos^2 x \cos^2 (x + y). \end{align*} 
